{"TopicId":220613,"ForumId":201,"TopicTitle":"Navball Incorrect [Navball Does Not Update To New Control Point After Undocking]","CreatedByName":"PT_P","CreatedById":228180,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-03T19:37:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"PT_P","CreatedById":228180,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-03T19:37:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Ryzen 5 2600 | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Radeon RX6650xt | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32gb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNavball maintains the pointing direction of the last craft after detaching from it.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn the screenshot attached below the navball is pointed at the horizon, but the actual module being controlled is pointing downward. This can be solved by opening the parts manager and changing control point.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png?ex=6557bfb1\u0026amp;is=65454ab1\u0026amp;hm=0d6\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/808434056635219988/1170082979368947722/image.png?ex=6557bfb1\u0026amp;is=65454ab1\u0026amp;hm=0d61dd64cc2f8fd95afe78ff9bdef79a388a4064a434b70be013d28d2011043e\u0026amp;\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-03T19:50:28Z\u0022 title=\u002211/03/2023 07:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 3\u0022\u003ENovember 3, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u0